# vim:set syntax=kconfig:
config CONFIG_HDDTEMP
  bool "hddtemp - small utility to read hard drive temperature"
  default n
  help
    hddtemp is a small utility that gives you the temperature of your hard
    drive by reading S.M.A.R.T. informations (for drives that support this
    feature).
    Note: only recent hard drives have a temperature sensor.

    http://www.guzu.net/linux/hddtemp.php
